250 g Ground Beef and Pork Mix
2 unit(s) Russet Potato
½ unit(s) Iceberg Lettuce Head
113 g Mirepoix
1 unit(s) Sweet Bell Pepper
4 tbsp Tomato Sauce Base
4 tbsp Mayonnaise
7 g Applewood Smoke Spice
1 unit(s) Beef Broth Concentrate
1 tbsp Whole Grain Mustard
1 unit(s) Honey
2 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, preheat the oven to 450˚F. Wash and dry all produce.
Remove any brown spots from potatoes, then cut into 1/4-inch rounds.
To a parchment-lined baking sheet, add potatoes, half the Applewood Smoke Spice and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil. (NOTE: For 4 servings, use 2 baking sheets, with 1 tbsp oil per sheet.) Season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat.
Roast in the middle of the oven for 22-25 min, flipping halfway, until tender and golden. (NOTE: For 4 servings, roast in the middle and top of the oven, rotating sheets halfway through.)

Heat a large non-stick pan over high.
While pan heats, core, then cut pepper into 1/4-inch pieces.
When the pan is hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, peppers and mirepoix. Cook for 2-4 min, stirring often, until tender crisp.
Transfer veggies to a medium bowl.

Reheat the same pan over medium-high.
When hot, add beef and pork mix to the dry pan.
Cook 4-5 min, breaking up meat into smaller pieces, until no pink remains.**
Add veggies, tomato sauce base, broth concentrate, half the honey, remaining Applewood Smoke Spice and 2 tbsp (1/4 cup) water. Season with salt and pepper. Cook for 1-2 min, stirring often, until fragrant.
Remove from heat.

To a small bowl, add mayo, mustard and remaining honey. Season with salt and pepper. Stir to mix.
Remove and discard outer layer of iceberg lettuce. Halve lettuce, then separate 8(16) leaves from the head. (NOTE: Save any remaining lettuce for a future creation!)

Divide potato coins and lettuce leaves between plates, layering lettuce as necessary to create small wraps.
Carefully spoon meat mixture into each lettuce wrap.
Serve honey-mustard mayo alongside for dipping.